NOTICE OF ASSESSMENT LIEN
CARACOL CREEK ASSOCIATION, INC
File No .: 83 - 341-4020
STATE OF TEXAS
COUNTY OF BEXAR
WHEREAS, that certain Declaration of Covenants, Conditions and Restrictions for Caracol Creek Association, Inc (hereinafter
"Association""), recorded in/under Volume 9543, Pages 85 of the Real Property Records of Bexar County, Texas (hereinafter
"Declaration") provides for a lien against the property located at 435 Territory Oak, San Antonio, TX 78253 (hereinafter
"Property") for the benefit of the Association to secure the payment of assessments levied against the Property for common
expenses and fees.
WHEREAS, the Declaration provides that the Association is vested with the power to assess, collect assessments, and enforce the
Jien retained against the Property.
WHEREAS, according to the Association's records, JOSEPH R. MENDIOLA, LAURA M. MENDIOLA whose address is
435 Territory Oak, San Antonio, Texas 78253, (hereinafter "Owner," whether one or more) is the Owner of the Property
legally described as follows:
Lot 20, Block 3, Caracol Creek Subdivision, Unit I, Bexar County, Texas,
according to the map or plat of record in Volume 9543, Page 85, Deed and Plat
Records of Bexar County, Texas.
WHEREAS, Owner is in default in the Owner's obligations to make payments for assessments and has failed, despite demand
upon the Owner, to pay Association assessments, handling charges, and collection costs properly levied against the Property, in
the amount as of 04/18/2022 equal to $1,300.97, which amount may continue to increase.
NOW THEREFORE, the Association, acting by and through a member of its Board of Directors, its duly authorized agent,
and/or its attorney, does hereby file this Notice of Assessment Lien against the Property due to non-payment of the amounts
contained herein as of the date set forth above.
EXECUTED this 5 day of __ Ley
